# Telco Customer Churn Prediction

## Academic Project
Completed as part of IST 615 – Business Intelligence Systems at Cleveland State University.

## Project Overview
This project predicts customer churn using Machine Learning and Business Intelligence techniques on the IBM Telco Customer Churn dataset.

## Objectives
- Analyze customer churn behavior
- Clean and preprocess customer data
- Build a Logistic Regression prediction model
- Evaluate model performance
- Recommend customer retention strategies

## Tools & Technologies
- Python
- Pandas
- NumPy
- Scikit-Learn
- Matplotlib
- Jupyter Notebook

## Model Used
- Logistic Regression

## Results
- Accuracy: 75.44%
- Precision: 52.59%
- Recall: 75.94%
- F1 Score: 62.14%
- ROC-AUC: 84.01%

## Key Findings
- Customers with short tenure are more likely to churn.
- Customers with high monthly charges have higher churn risk.
- Month-to-month contracts show higher churn rates.

